  "definition": "Peptide from the anterior pituitary that stimulates the adrenal cortex (zona fasciculata) → cortisol. [[crh]] ↑ ACTH; chronic ↑ causes adrenal hyperplasia.",

  "mnemonics": [
    "A C T H → Adrenal Cortex To Hormone (cortisol)",
    "CRH → ACTH → Cortisol"
  ],

  "pitfalls": [
    "Don’t confuse Cushing *disease* (pituitary ACTH excess) with Cushing *syndrome* (any cause of cortisol excess).",
    "Hyperpigmentation in primary adrenal failure is ACTH‑driven (↑MSH)."
  ],

